# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok south korean teenager noh seung-yul shot a six-under-par ## wednesday to share the opening round lead with danny chia of malaysia at british open qualifying for asia .
# ::alignments
(s / shoot-02
      :ARG0 (t / teenager
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Noh"
                  :op2 "Seung-yul")
            :location (c / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "South"
                        :op2 "Korea")))
      :ARG1 (u / under
            :op1 (p / par-03)
            :quant (s2 / score-entity
                  :quant 6))
      :time (w / wednesday)
      :purpose (s3 / share-01
            :ARG0 t
            :ARG1 (l / lead-02
                  :ARG0 t
                  :ARG2 (r / round
                        :ARG1-of (o / open-02)))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "Malaysia")
                  :mod (c3 / country
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "Britain")))
            :subevent-of (q / qualify-02
                  :ARG1 c2
                  :ARG2 c3
                  :ARG1-of (o2 / open-02))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :op2 "House"))

            :ARG0 g

                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (p / person
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Karl"
                                    :op2 "Rove")

                                    :ARG1 (p2 / politics)))
                        :op2 (p3 / person
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Harriet"
                                    :op2 "Miers")
                              :ARG0-of (c / counsel-01
                                    :time (f / former))))
                  :ARG2 (ii / interview-01
                        :ARG0 (c2 / committee
                              :mod (g2 / government-organization
                                    :name (n4 / name
                                          :op1 "Congress"))
                              :ARG0-of (ii2 / investigate-01
                                    :ARG1 (f2 / fire-02
                                          :ARG1 (p4 / person
                                                :quant 8
                                                :ARG0-of (p5 / prosecute-01)
                                                :mod (f3 / federal)))))
                        :ARG1 a2
                        :manner (u / under
                              :op1 (o2 / oath))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / tuesday))))

                  :time (d / date-interval
                        :op1 (d2 / date-entity
                              :season (s / summer)
                              :mod (y / year))
                        :op2 (d3 / date-entity
                              :season (f / fall)
                              :mod (y2 / year))))
            :ARG2 (b2 / back))
      :ARG1 (l / last-03
            :ARG1 (r / restructure-01
                  :ARG1 c
                  :mod (c2 / complex))
            :ARG2 (c3 / close-to
                  :op1 (t2 / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 3
                        :unit (y3 / year)))
            :time (n2 / now)
            :ARG1-of (h / have-degree-91
                  :ARG2 (l2 / long-03
                        :ARG1 r)
                  :ARG3 (t3 / times
                        :quant 2)
                  :ARG4 (a / anticipate-01
                        :ARG1 r))))

                        :ARG2 (l / large)
                        :ARG3 (m / most)
                        :ARG5 (c / company
                              :ARG0-of (m2 / make-01
                                    :ARG1 (c2 / car))
                              :location (c3 / city
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Russia")))))
            :ARG2 (j / job)
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (m3 / monday))
            :time (a2 / after
                  :op1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (b / begin-01
                              :ARG0 (c4 / company
                                    :ARG0-of (m4 / manage-01))
                              :ARG1 (p2 / pay-01
                                    :ARG1 (w2 / wage
                                          :ARG1-of (d2 / date-entity
                                                :month 11))))
                        :op2 (a4 / agree-01
                              :ARG0 c4
